# Building a Custom Blog Theme

One of Chiron's most powerful features is its theming system. Let's create a custom blog theme from scratch.

## Understanding the Theme System

Chiron uses CSS variables from the Carbon Design System:

```css
:root {
  --color-primary: #0f62fe;
  --color-text: #161616;
  --space-md: 1rem;
  --radius-sm: 0.25rem;
}
```

Your custom styles automatically inherit these, ensuring consistency.

## Overriding Blog Styles

Create a `custom.css` file:

```css
.blog-post-card {
  border: 2px solid var(--color-primary);
  transition: transform var(--duration-fast);
}

.blog-post-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-8px);
}
```

The plugin's CSS is modular and easy to override.

## Custom Template Example

Here's a minimal custom `blog-post.ejs`:

```html
<%- include('head', { title: post.title }) %>
<%- include('header') %>

<article class="my-custom-post">
  <h1><%= post.title %></h1>
  <div class="meta">
    By <%= post.author %> on <%= post.date %>
  </div>
  <%- post.content %>
</article>

<%- include('footer') %>
```

Simple, powerful, yours.

## Responsive Design

All blog templates are mobile-first:

- Grid layouts that adapt to screen size
- Touch-friendly navigation
- Optimized image loading
- Readable typography at any scale

## Dark Mode Support

The theme system includes automatic dark mode:

```css
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  .blog-post {
    background: var(--color-background-dark);
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }
}
```

Works without any extra configuration! ðŸŒ™

